{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Teaching students to use LLMs for coding can also reduce inequities introduced by some students finding coding much harder than others.",
    "There are special advantages for neurodivergent students, and for students whose first language is not English.",
    "These benefits should also be considered when thinking about equity and inclusion in AI.",
    "As long as LLMs remain easy to access (and particularly while they remain free to use), students will use them whether educators like it or not.",
    "Our recommendation is to guide and advise students on responsible use of AI rather than attempting to regulate or ban its use (see also Duffy, 2024, Lubiana et al., 2023; and https://cs50.ai/)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Our recommendation is to guide and advise students on responsible use of AI rather than attempting to regulate or ban its use (see also Duffy, 2024, Lubiana et al., 2023; and https://cs50.ai/)."
  ]
